                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Fine, regular</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (vivid vermilion)</seg>
                        <date>Mid- or late 17th - mid-18th century.</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ቅ</abbr> for <expan>ቅዱስ </expan> (<locus target="#31rc">31rc</locus>, 33rc)</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; a few lines on the incipit page,
                           alternating with black lines; two initial lines of each sub-section of
                           the text; elements of punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals;
                           some words like kǝfl (e.g., fols. 151ra, 152ra, 155rb), yǝbe (e.g., fols.
                           153vb, 154ra), rabǝʿ (e.g., fols. 151ra, 156vc), tǝʿǝzaz (e.g., fols.
                           156vc, 157ra).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">At least two hands can be
                        discerned:</handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic"> Hand a: Text I
                        (fols.2ra-158ra)</handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h4" script="Ethiopic"> Hand b: Text II (<locus from="158ra" to="159vc">158ra-159vc</locus>)</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#159vc">f. 159vc</locus>
                           <desc>: Ownership note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#159vc">159vc</locus>: ዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘብሔረ፡ ስንቃጣ፡ ዘእግዝእት[ነ]፡
                              ማርያም፡ ዘሰረቃ፡ ወዘተአገላ፡ ወዘፈሐቃ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን፡ በሥልጣነ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ፡ ወእስከ፡ ለዓለመ፡
                              ዓለም፡ አሜን፡ ወአሜን። ለይኩን ለይኩን።</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en">
                              <locus target="#159vc">159vc</locus>: This book is of the country of
                              Sǝnqaṭa of Our Lady Mary. The one who stole it or took it by force or
                              erased it will be excommunicated by the Authority of Peter and Paul,
                              forever and ever, Amen and Amen. So be it, so be it.</quote>
                           <note> </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Writing exercises in the margins: <locus target="#2r">2r</locus>, 2v, 5r, 11rc, 17r, 58r, 59r, 60r, 119r, 
 -
                           Interlineal correction: <locus target="#10vc">10vc</locus>, 11rb, 43vc,
                           69ra, 72rc, 
 - Compressed script: <locus target="#11rc">11rc</locus>, 130vc.
 - A marginal note mentioning Māryām Sǝnqaṭa as
                           the owner of the Ms.: <locus target="#156v">156v</locus>.
 - Portion
                           of the text written in compressed script: <locus from="158vc" to="159rb">158vc-159rb</locus>.
 - The ownership note is rewritten by pen
                           immediately below the original: <locus target="#159vc">159vc</locus>.</item>
                     </list>
